==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sesquioxide
<hw>Ses`qui*ox"ide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Sesqui-</ets> + <ets>oxide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An oxide containing three atoms of oxygen with two atoms (or
radicals) of some other substance; <as>thus, alumina,
<chform>Al2O3</chform> is a <ex>sesquioxide</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

